<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">To compute these metrics for an atmospheric state ξ(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>
 <sub class="sub">1</sub>), corresponding to a point on the phase-space trajectory, we considered recurrences of the system around the said point. We defined the distance between the point of interest ξ(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>
 <sub class="sub">1</sub>) and all other observations ξ(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>) along the trajectory as
 <disp-formula class="disp-formula">
  <math id="m1" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">g</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mo class="mo">−</mo>
     <mtext class="mtext">log</mtext>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mtext class="mtext">dist</mtext>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">,</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>where dist is a distance function (in our case, the Euclidean distance between the SLP maps). The logarithm was applied to increase the discrimination of close recurrences. Following the Freitas-Freitas-Todd theorem (
 <xref rid="R38" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">
  <italic class="italic">38</italic>
 </xref>), modified by Lucarini 
 <italic class="italic">et al.</italic> (
 <xref rid="R39" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">
  <italic class="italic">39</italic>
 </xref>), the probability of a recurrence within a hypersphere of radius η centered on ξ(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>
 <sub class="sub">1</sub>) converges to a generalized Pareto distribution
 <disp-formula class="disp-formula">
  <math id="m2" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">P</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">g</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">&gt;</mo>
     <mi class="mi">q</mi>
     <mo class="mo">,</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">≃</mo>
     <msup class="msup">
      <mi class="mi">e</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ϑ</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">t</mi>
        <mn class="mn">1</mn>
       </msub>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
       <mfrac class="mfrac">
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">g</mi>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
         <mi class="mi">t</mi>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">μ</mi>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">t</mi>
          <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         </msub>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">σ</mi>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ξ</mi>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">t</mi>
          <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         </msub>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
       </mfrac>
       <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </msup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>where the radius can be related to a high threshold 
 <italic class="italic">q</italic> by
 <disp-formula class="disp-formula">
  <math id="m3" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">η</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <msup class="msup">
      <mi class="mi">e</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <mi class="mi">q</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
